      <span class="w-100 block bold h6 bb">CSS</span>
      The default state for accordions is to have a background color equal to <span><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-selector-tag">var</span>(<span class="hljs-attr">--secondary-background</span>)</code></span> and to have 
      padding that changes based on the <span style="position: relative;"><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">details</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> element open state.
      <br>
      The details element can be made to have a transparent background by adding the <span><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-selector-class">.flat</span></code></span> class to the details element.
      <br>
      The <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">summary</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> element should have the class <span><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-selector-class">.accordion-content</span></code></span> for the JavaScript to work correctly. This class also gives the accordion content some padding to make it look slightly indented.
      <br />
      Here is how a normal accordion should look:
    <div style="position: relative;"><pre class="hz-scroll"><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">details</span> <span class="hljs-attr">open</span> <span class="hljs-attr">aria-label</span>=<span class="hljs-string">&quot;TITLE&quot;</span>&gt;</span>
