          <br/>
          If the <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">details</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> element is a direct child of an <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">ul</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span>, and <em class="bold">if</em> the 
          <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">ul</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> has the class <span><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-selector-class">.accordion</span></code></span> and the attribute <span class="t-info bold">data-only</span>, then the javascript toggles the currently open 
          <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">details</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> element and 
          opens the recently clicked <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">details</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> element whenever a summary element is clicked.
      <span class="w-100 block bold h6 mt-2 bb">Accessability</span>
      The content in the <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">summary</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> should be hidden from screen readers 
      unless the <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">details</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> element is open.
      <br/>
      The <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">details</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> element should have an <span class="t-info">aria-label</span> attribute.
